        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated values. Global production volume for mineral fibers is 9 billion kg/year (Buchel at el. 2000, p. 373). 
The waste generation is estimated to be 15% (taken from the estimated value for gypsum, source: WRAP "International practice in plasterboard recycling: Canada", n.d).
From previous version of ecoinvent, 41% of waste goes to landfill (70% of this is assumed to go to inert material, based on ration applied in version 2 to other C&amp;D wastes, such as gypsum), 41% goes directly to recycling, and 18% is sent for sorting.
References:
Buchel, K.H. et al. (2000) Industrial Inorganic Chemistry. Wiley-VCH. 
WRAP (n.d.) International practice in plasterboard recycling: Canada. Retrieved from: http://www.wrap.org.uk/sites/files/wrap/Case%20study%20-%20Plasterboard%20recycling%20in%20Canada.pdf, accessed 3 May 2016
</productionVolumeComment>
